modules.description: This module defines a message type for handling MQTT communication, including operations to create messages with optional message IDs, quality of service levels, and retention flags. It provides accessors to retrieve message metadata such as topic, QoS level, and payload content. Concrete use cases include constructing and inspecting MQTT messages for publishing or processing incoming messages in an MQTT client application.

This module provides direct access to the version numbers of the Mosquitto library, including the full version, major, minor, and revision components. It works with integer values representing version segments. Use this module to check or compare the Mosquitto library version at runtime, for example to enable features or workarounds based on version constraints.

This module implements an interface for interacting with the Mosquitto MQTT library, enabling clients to connect to MQTT brokers, publish messages, and subscribe to topics. It provides functions for creating and managing MQTT connections, sending and receiving messages with configurable QoS levels, and setting callbacks for connection events, message arrivals, and logging. Concrete use cases include building MQTT-based IoT communication systems, real-time data streaming applications, and networked device control systems.
